        <h2>1. Contractor Foreman — Best overall for framing subs</h2>
        <p><strong>Pricing:</strong> Basic $49/mo · Standard $79/mo · Pro $159/mo · Unlimited $299/mo</p>

        <p>Contractor Foreman gives framing contractors the essentials without the overhead of enterprise pricing. Estimating, scheduling, time tracking, and job costing are all included. For a framing sub doing 20–50 residential frames per year, this covers 90% of what you actually need.</p>

        <p><strong>Key strengths for framers:</strong></p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Bid management:</strong> Create and track bids for incoming GC requests</li>
          <li><strong>Crew time tracking:</strong> Mobile clock-in/out by job — compare labor hours to estimate</li>
          <li><strong>Material tracking:</strong> Log lumber deliveries and materials against each job</li>
          <li><strong>Scheduling:</strong> Calendar view with crew assignments across multiple active jobs</li>
          <li><strong>Purchase orders:</strong> Send POs to your lumber yard directly from a job</li>
          <li><strong>Document storage:</strong> Attach plans, cut lists, and contracts to each job</li>
        </ul>

        <p><strong>Limitations:</strong></p>
        <ul>
          <li>No digital plan takeoff — enter quantities manually</li>
          <li>UI isn't as clean as newer platforms</li>
          <li>Support response can be slow on weekends</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>2. Jobber — Best for fast-moving framing crews</h2>
        <p><strong>Pricing:</strong> Core $69/mo · Connect $169/mo · Grow $349/mo</p>

        <p>Jobber is built for speed: fast quotes, quick scheduling, easy invoicing. If you're framing production homes and need to get quotes out same-day, Jobber's streamlined interface gets it done faster than most platforms. It's less comprehensive than Contractor Foreman but cleaner to use.</p>

        <p><strong>Key strengths:</strong></p>
        <ul>
          <li>Quote creation and client approval in minutes</li>
          <li>Crew scheduling with GPS check-in</li>
          <li>Automated payment reminders and online payment portal</li>
          <li>Client hub for job communication and approvals</li>
        </ul>

        <p><strong>Limitations:</strong></p>
        <ul>
          <li>Job costing is basic compared to Contractor Foreman or JobTread</li>
          <li>Not ideal if you need detailed lumber cost tracking by phase</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>3. JobTread — Best for framing companies with estimating depth</h2>
        <p><strong>Pricing:</strong> Basic $99/mo · Standard $199/mo · Pro $349/mo</p>

        <p>JobTread's strength is its estimate-to-job-cost workflow. You build a framing estimate with material, labor, and sub costs broken out, set markup, and the system generates a professional proposal. When the GC approves, the estimate becomes your job budget automatically. As actual costs come in, you can see exactly where you're over or under.</p>

        <p>For framing contractors who want better profit visibility, this cost-tracking discipline is worth the premium over Contractor Foreman.</p>

